cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a network model and performance evaluation of a multihop relaying system. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses the signal-to-interference-and-noise ratio capture condition and evaluates the performance characteristics related to packet relaying. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper studies the impact of additional fixed relaying nodes on the routing performance. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the performance characteristics of a system with multiple nodes and interference. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on algorithmic or data structure aspects, but rather on the performance evaluation of a network model.
